init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the â€œLost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You were a bit of a rebel in your youth, but you had grown up to be a very responsible adult.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The announcement that the drug had been discovered to have side effects.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The government had been working on a cure for the side effects, but it was too late.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But then, a second scientist suggested that they could use the "Lost Generations" as test subjects.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And so, you were injected with a serum that was supposed to cure the side effects.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And then, one day, they found a serum that worked.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And so, the world was saved.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And so, you died, happy that your children and grandchildren would be able to live a long and happy life.
